\section{PROJECTS}
\label{sec:org322e1b3}

\begin{itemize}
\item Bruce compiled the 2.18 kernel tweaking the device drivers and fitting the available drivers. On numerous occassions Bruce compiled a full monolithic kernel and successfully ran his machine.
\item Bruce constructed his own Linux systems, researching required hardware and available drivers.
\item Bruce installed a picoITX form factor PC using a 12V DC ATX power supply in his caravan.
\item Bruce tweaked the FreeBSD USB driver to pick up his USB device which had an unknown IC and an unusual signature.
\item Bruce used lithographic principles to build his own hand made circuit board.
\item Bruce conducted a 'from scratch' analysis of his expenses in R, attempting to incorporate work from his actuarial studies on ruin theory.
\item Bruce made various attempts at creating an insightful Dashboard for his portfolio of equities.
\end{itemize}

